messages.title: What's at stake
messages.content: Five years ago, the Labour Minister in charge of spending taxpayers' money left us a note saying: 'I'm afraid there is no money.' Five years on, the Conservatives are building a stronger economy, and securing a better and brighter future for all of us.

messages.title: What's at risk
messages.content: The last five years of economic progress could easily be lost if the Conservatives don't act.

messages.title: Your vote will be the difference
messages.content: The Conservatives only need to win 23 more seats to form a majority government – and keep Ed Miliband and the SNP out of Downing Street.

leaflet.additionalNotes: The leaflet emphasizes the risk of an SNP-Labour alliance and encourages strategic voting to prevent this outcome. Employment rate at 'record high' is also a message conveyed.
